Help for FLAGS:

The FLAGS command allows for channel privilege granting/removal
on a more specific, non-generalized level. It supports both
user accounts and hostmasks as targets.

When given only the channel argument, a listing of permissions
granted to users will be displayed.

Syntax: FLAGS <#channel> [username|hostmask] [flags]

Permissions:
    +v - Enables use of the voice/devoice commands.
    +V - Enables automatic voicing.
    +o - Enables use of the op/deop commands.
    +O - Enables automatic op.
    +s - Enables use of the set command.
    +i - Enables use of the invite command.
    +r - Enables use of the kick, ban, akick and kickban commands.
    +R - Enables use of the recover command.
    +f - Enables use of the flags command.
    +t - Enables use of the topic and topicappend commands.
    +b - Enables automatic kickban.
    +* - All of the above.

Examples:
    /msg &nick& FLAGS #foo
    /msg &nick& FLAGS #foo foo!*@bar.com +vV
    /msg &nick& FLAGS #foo foo!*@bar.com -vV
    /msg &nick& FLAGS #foo foo!*@bar.com -*
    /msg &nick& FLAGS #foo foo +oOtsi
    /msg &nick& FLAGS #foo TroubleUser!*@*.troubleisp.net +b
